  "dataFlow": "1. INBOUND TRIGGERS: A build is initiated via (a) browser POST /api/build with cookie auth, (b) GitHub/Linear webhook HMAC-verified POST /api/webhook, (c) autonomy poller polling Linear GraphQL every 5 min, or (d) cron engine firing from cron-triggers.json. 2. SESSION CREATION: create_session() in sessions.py allocates a BuildSession object in the in-memory _sessions dict, persists initial JSON to app/logs/.sessions/{sid}.json via os.replace() atomic write, and enqueues run_build() as an asyncio task. 3. BUILD PIPELINE: run_build() executes 5 phases sequentially — (a) clone: git clone --depth 1 into app/workspaces/{sid}/, (b) plan: Claude Agent SDK session decomposes brief via PITER classifier and selects ADW template, (c) generate: _run_claude_via_sdk() spawns a ClaudeSDKClient with bypassPermissions, streams JSON events, appends to session.output_lines, emits to WebSocket/SSE, (d) evaluate: second ClaudeSDKClient grades git diff on 4 dimensions against configurable threshold, (e) ship: git commit and push via configured credentials. Each phase writes a checkpoint to disk. 4. REAL-TIME OUTPUT: session.output_lines are broadcast concurrently to (a) WebSocket /ws/build/{sid} with 150ms polling, and (b) SSE /api/sessions/{sid}/logs with 300ms polling. 5. OBSERVABILITY: supabase_log.py fire-and-forgets every gate_check and alert_escalation row to Supabase PostgreSQL. SDK invocations emit JSONL metrics to .harness/agent-sdk-metrics/YYYY-MM-DD.jsonl. 6. LINEAR SYNC: on terminal session state, the webhook handler or autonomy poller calls Linear GraphQL to update issue state. 7. TELEGRAM ALERTS: triage.py and marathon_watchdog.py push critical alerts outbound via urllib POST to api.telegram.org; inbound commands arrive at POST /webhook/telegram and are processed synchronously. 8. MCP READS: Claude Desktop calls mcp/pi-ceo-server.js tools over stdio JSON-RPC 2.0; the server reads .harness/ markdown/JSON files and returns structured data — no writes except via linear_create_issue. 9. DASHBOARD ANALYSIS: Next.js API routes call @anthropic-ai/sdk directly (ANALYSIS_MODE=api) or shell out to claude CLI (ANALYSIS_MODE=cli); results are rendered in the browser without round-tripping the FastAPI backend. 10. SCANNING: Pi-SEO scanner clones repos into SCAN_WORKSPACE_ROOT, runs 4 scan types, writes JSON to .harness/scan-results/, triage engine reads results and calls Linear API to create tickets, monitor agent compares across cycles and writes digest to .harness/monitor-digests/.",
